🔹 Configuration 1: default.conf (Official tester setup)

Run:
./webserv

◉ Basic HTTP tests:
curl -i http://localhost:8080/
→ Expect: 200 OK

curl -i -X POST http://localhost:8080/
→ Expect: 405 Method Not Allowed

curl -i -X POST http://localhost:8080/post_body -d "1234567890"
→ Expect: 200 OK

curl -i -X POST http://localhost:8080/post_body -d "$(python3 -c 'print("a"*101)')"
→ Expect: 413 Payload Too Large

◉ Directory / alias tests:
curl -i http://localhost:8080/directory/
→ Expect: 200 OK

curl -i http://localhost:8080/directory/nop/youpi.bad_extension
→ Expect: 200 OK

◉ CGI by extension (.bla):
curl -i -X POST http://localhost:8080/directory/youpi.bla -d "hello"
→ Expect: CGI executed (cgi_test output)

🔹 Configuration 2: manual_test.conf (Development & extended testing)

Run:
./webserv configs/manual_test.conf

◉ Basic HTTP tests:
curl -i http://localhost:8080/
curl -i -X POST http://localhost:8080/
curl -i -X POST http://localhost:8080/post_body -d "1234567890"
curl -i -X POST http://localhost:8080/post_body -d "$(python3 -c 'print("a"*101)')"

◉ Advanced routing tests:
curl -i http://localhost:8080/red
→ Expect: redirect (302 + Location header)

curl -i http://localhost:8080/does-not-exist
→ Expect: custom 404 page

curl -i http://localhost:8080/tours
→ Expect: tours1.html content

◉ Directory / alias tests:
curl -i http://localhost:8080/directory/
→ Expect: 200 OK and the contents of youpi.bad_extension (if the file is not empty)

curl -i http://localhost:8080/directory/nop/
→ Expect: 200 OK and the contents of nop/youpi.bad_extension (if the file is not empty)

◉ CGI tests:
curl -i http://localhost:8080/cgi-bin/time.py
curl -i "http://localhost:8080/cgi-bin/time.py?name=maria&x=1"
curl -i -X POST http://localhost:8080/cgi-bin/time.py -d "hello=world"

◉ Additional method test:
curl -i -X DELETE http://localhost:8080/tours1.html

◉ Chunked request test:
printf 'POST /cgi-bin/time.py HTTP/1.1\r\nHost: localhost:8080\r\nTransfer-Encoding: chunked\r\n\r\n5\r\nhello\r\n0\r\n\r\n' | nc localhost 8080

→ Expect:
- no crash
- valid HTTP response
- CGI receives decoded body